{"books":{"7":{"id":"8728","title":"From Passion to Peace","description":"The first three parts of this book, Passion, Aspiration, and Temptation, represent the common human life, with its passion, pathos, and tragedy. The last three parts, Transcendence, Beatitude, and Peace, represents the Divine Life\u2014calm, wise and beautiful\u2014of the sage and Savior. The middle part, Transmutation, is the transitional stage between the two; it is the alchemic process linking the divine with the human life. Discipline, denial, and renunciation do not constitute the Divine State; they are only the means by which it is attained. The Divine Life is established in that Perfect Knowledge which bestows Perfect Peace. - Summary by James Allen<p>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/james-allen.in1woord.nl\/?text=from-passion-to-peace","language":"English","copyright_year":"1910","num_sections":"8","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/8728","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/\/passiontopeace_1403_librivox\/passiontopeace_1403_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/from-passion-to-peace-by-james-allen\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"01:03:43","totaltimesecs":3823,"authors":[{"id":"1323","first_name":"James","last_name":"Allen","dob":"1864","dod":"1912"}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/archive.org\/details\/passiontopeace_1403_librivox","sections":[{"id":"307154","section_number":"0","title":"Forward","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/rapunzelina\/passiontopeace_00_allen_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"118","file_name":"passiontopeace_00_allen_128kb.mp3","readers":[{"reader_id":"2196","display_name":"Andrea Fiore"}]},{"id":"307155","section_number":"1","title":"Passion","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/rapunzelina\/passiontopeace_01_allen_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"521","file_name":"passiontopeace_01_allen_128kb.mp3","readers":[{"reader_id":"2196","display_name":"Andrea Fiore"}]},{"